arch:property.oc:show_val: Ledge in front of West Semicircular Niche

Phase VI: Late Nabataean pre CE 106 minor collapses and repairs. Probable early collapse of the Baroque Room and damage occurs in both the Anteroom and Shrine Room. The tabun in Room A is used to store CE 1st c. Nabataean fine wares. East 'Cistern" used as a dump. Bath Complex built.
0.70 m north south-by- 0.40 m east west.
In the west of the trench in front of Locus 5.

The ledge was necessary for removal in order to clear the semicircular nicheÂ’s deposition. It architecturally provided a barrier or perhaps a support for the vessels that were used to remove the water from the area below.
Construction of the Well Room and the canalization system.
